-- Giants Score to Tie 49ers 7-7 in Second Quarter of NFC Championship Game
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2012-01-23T00:33:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-23/giants-score-to-tie-49ers-7-7-in-second-quarter-of-nfc-championship-game.html
The New York Giants scored a
touchdown to tie the San Francisco 49ers 7-7 in the second
quarter of the National Football Conference championship game.  The winner will play the  New England Patriots  in the  Super
Bowl  in Indianapolis on Feb. 5. New England beat Baltimore 23-20
in the American Football Conference championship game today.  Ravens kicker Billy Cundiff missed a 32-yard field goal
that would have tied the game with 11 seconds to play. Tom Brady
scored the go-ahead touchdown for New England on a 1-yard run
with 4 minutes, 21 seconds left at Gillette Stadium in
Foxborough, Massachusetts.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  